1
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:11,846
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

2
00:00:11,887 --> 00:00:14,640
MAN: I NEED
THREE MORE CONTAINERS.

3
00:00:14,682 --> 00:00:16,475
BRING THEM TO ME.

4
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:18,226
SECOND MAN: YEAH.

5
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:20,646
THIRD MAN: WE HAVE TWO TYPES.

6
00:00:20,688 --> 00:00:24,566
FOURTH MAN: I'M ON IT.
WE'RE DOWN 22%. TELL HIM.

7
00:00:48,007 --> 00:00:50,384
[ AIRCRAFT APPROACHING ]

8
00:00:56,807 --> 00:00:58,225
IS IT THEM?

9
00:00:58,266 --> 00:01:01,102
MAN: I DON'T KNOW.

10
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:02,563
NO.

11
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:04,940
IT'S NOT THEIR SHIP.

12
00:01:04,982 --> 00:01:07,693
IT'S SOMEONE ELSE.

13
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:28,839
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

14
00:01:28,881 --> 00:01:32,091
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

15
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:35,971
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

16
00:01:36,013 --> 00:01:39,516
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

17
00:01:39,558 --> 00:01:44,021
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

18
00:01:44,063 --> 00:01:47,482
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

19
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:51,486
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

20
00:01:51,528 --> 00:01:54,615
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

21
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:57,325
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

22
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:59,494
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

23
00:01:59,536 --> 00:02:02,414
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

24
00:02:02,456 --> 00:02:07,252
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

25
00:02:07,294 --> 00:02:10,505
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

26
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:14,760
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

27
00:02:14,802 --> 00:02:17,972
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

28
00:02:18,013 --> 00:02:23,602
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

29
00:02:23,644 --> 00:02:25,646
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

30
00:02:25,687 --> 00:02:27,940
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

31
00:02:27,982 --> 00:02:31,526
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

32
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:36,323
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

33
00:03:03,809 --> 00:03:05,602
ARCHER:
MY NAME IS CAPTAIN ARCHER

34
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:07,771
FROM THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

35
00:03:07,813 --> 00:03:10,149
WE TRIED TO HAIL YOU,
BUT THERE WAS NO RESPONSE.

36
00:03:10,189 --> 00:03:12,609
FIRST MAN: OUR COMMUNICATIONS
ARE DOWN.

37
00:03:12,651 --> 00:03:15,403
THAT MUST MAKE IT DIFFICULT
TO DO BUSINESS.

38
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:22,077
A KREETASSAN MERCHANT TOLD US
THIS WAS A DEUTERIUM FACILITY.

39
00:03:22,119 --> 00:03:23,662
FIRST MAN: HE WAS CORRECT.

40
00:03:23,704 --> 00:03:25,455
TUCKER: OUR SHIP TOOK
SOME DAMAGE A FEW WEEKS AGO.

41
00:03:25,497 --> 00:03:26,915
WE LOST MOST OF OUR RESERVES.

42
00:03:26,957 --> 00:03:28,625
FIRST MAN: I'M SORRY,
BUT WE CAN'T HELP YOU.

43
00:03:28,667 --> 00:03:31,837
TWO OF OUR PUMPS ARE OFFLINE.

44
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:33,547
YOU'LL HAVE TO RETURN
LATER IN THE SEASON.

45
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:35,924
OUR SUPPLY WILL BE GONE
IN LESS THAN TWO WEEKS.

46
00:03:35,966 --> 00:03:37,467
THERE'S NOTHING WE CAN DO.

47
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:39,219
ARE YOU CERTAIN?

48
00:03:39,260 --> 00:03:40,971
YOU SEEM TO HAVE
A LARGE INVENTORY.

49
00:03:41,013 --> 00:03:43,974
OUR SENSORS SHOWED
OVER 80,000 LITERS.

50
00:03:44,016 --> 00:03:45,600
YOU SCANNED OUR TANKS?

51
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:49,063
I APOLOGIZE, BUT WHEN YOU DIDN'T
RESPOND TO OUR HAILS...

52
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:53,859
YOU SURE YOU COULDN'T SPARE
A FEW HUNDRED LITERS?

53
00:03:53,901 --> 00:03:55,194
FIRST MAN: WE'RE HOLDING THAT
FOR SOMEONE ELSE.

54
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:56,778
COME BACK AT THE END
OF THE SEASON.

55
00:03:56,820 --> 00:03:58,864
I'M SURE WE'LL BE ABLE
TO ACCOMMODATE YOU.

56
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:00,574
SECOND MAN: DO YOU HAVE
ANY EXPERIENCE

57
00:04:00,615 --> 00:04:02,492
REPAIRING EXTRACTION PUMPS?

58
00:04:02,534 --> 00:04:04,078
TUCKER: NOT SPECIFICALLY,

59
00:04:04,119 --> 00:04:07,039
BUT I COULD GRAB SOME TOOLS
AND TAKE A LOOK.

60
00:04:07,081 --> 00:04:09,124
SECOND MAN: IF WE
GET THOSE PUMPS OPERATING,

61
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:11,085
WE CAN MAKE OUR QUOTA.

62
00:04:11,126 --> 00:04:13,503
IT SEEMS THAT THERE
MIGHT BE AN OPPORTUNITY

63
00:04:13,545 --> 00:04:16,006
FOR US TO HELP EACH OTHER.

64
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:20,010
FIRST MAN: FOLLOW ME.

65
00:04:39,196 --> 00:04:41,990
[ BOY IMITATES EXPLOSIONS ]

66
00:04:48,247 --> 00:04:49,414
[ MACHINE BEEPS ]

67
00:04:49,456 --> 00:04:51,250
[ BOY GASPS ]

68
00:04:52,793 --> 00:04:55,170
TUCKER: WHAT ARE YOU DOING
IN MY CHAIR?

69
00:04:55,212 --> 00:04:58,673
BOY: UM, I--I DIDN'T
TOUCH ANYTHING.

70
00:04:58,715 --> 00:05:02,719
I JUST LIKE TO LOOK
INSIDE THE SHIPS THAT COME HERE.

71
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:04,387
TUCKER: WELL,
YOU SHOULD'VE ASKED.

72
00:05:04,429 --> 00:05:06,473
BOY: YOU MIGHT HAVE SAID NO.

73
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:10,477
WELL...

74
00:05:10,518 --> 00:05:12,187
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

75
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,023
WELL, IT'S A LITTLE SMALL,

76
00:05:15,065 --> 00:05:17,442
AND YOUR THRUSTER CONTROLS
ARE HARD TO REACH.

77
00:05:17,484 --> 00:05:20,988
OH. WELL, MAYBE YOU NEED
LONGER ARMS.

78
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:24,741
HOW FAST CAN IT GO?

79
00:05:24,783 --> 00:05:26,952
SHE'S DESIGNED
FOR ONE-QUARTER IMPULSE,

80
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:29,496
BUT, UH, I'VE BEEN
ABLE TO SQUEEZE

81
00:05:29,537 --> 00:05:31,206
A LITTLE MORE OUT OF HER.

82
00:05:31,248 --> 00:05:32,874
BOY: YOU'RE A PILOT?

83
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:34,168
TUCKER: ENGINEER.

84
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:35,585
COMMANDER TRIP TUCKER.

85
00:05:35,627 --> 00:05:37,171
Q'ELL.

86
00:05:37,212 --> 00:05:38,505
NICE TO MEET YOU.

87
00:05:38,546 --> 00:05:40,548
COULD YOU TEACH ME
HOW TO FLY IT?

88
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:42,134
[ CHUCKLES ]

89
00:05:42,176 --> 00:05:44,303
I CAN DRIVE THE CRAWLER THAT
WE USE TO MOVE OUR DRILL RIGS.

90
00:05:44,343 --> 00:05:46,680
TELL YOU WHAT.

91
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:49,266
I'LL BE HEADING BACK UP
TO THE SHIP LATER.

92
00:05:49,308 --> 00:05:52,102
YOU CAN COME ALONG IF IT'S
ALL RIGHT WITH YOUR FOLKS.

93
00:05:52,144 --> 00:05:53,520
I'LL GIVE YOU A TOUR.

94
00:05:53,561 --> 00:05:56,523
REALLY?

95
00:05:56,564 --> 00:06:00,652
FIRST MAN: TWO POWER CELLS...
WE NEED SIX.

96
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:04,614
ARCHER: WE CAN'T SPARE
THAT MANY.

97
00:06:04,656 --> 00:06:06,658
MAYBE THREE.

98
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:08,702
FIRST MAN: DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW MUCH LABOR IT TAKES

99
00:06:08,743 --> 00:06:10,954
TO REFINE A LITER OF DEUTERIUM?

100
00:06:10,996 --> 00:06:13,915
ARCHER: ACTUALLY, NO.

101
00:06:13,957 --> 00:06:17,211
I'D ENJOY SEEING
HOW YOUR FACILITY WORKS.

102
00:06:17,252 --> 00:06:19,338
WE HAVE THREE MONTHS
OF GOOD WEATHER, CAPTAIN--

103
00:06:19,378 --> 00:06:21,923
THREE MONTHS TO PUMP
ALL THE DEUTERIUM WE CAN

104
00:06:21,965 --> 00:06:23,591
BEFORE THE WINTER.

105
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:26,720
WE DON'T HAVE TIME
TO GIVE TOURS.

106
00:06:26,761 --> 00:06:31,225
FIVE POWER CELLS FOR 200 LITERS.
I CAN'T DO ANY BETTER.

107
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:36,521
OUR MEDICAL STORES
ARE RUNNING LOW.

108
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:42,152
ARCHER: FOUR POWER CELLS

109
00:06:42,194 --> 00:06:45,488
AND WHATEVER MEDICAL SUPPLIES
WE CAN SPARE.

110
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:50,827
ALL RIGHT.

111
00:06:50,869 --> 00:06:53,330
BUT ONLY
IF YOU CAN REPAIR OUR PUMPS.

112
00:06:53,372 --> 00:06:56,624
COMMANDER TUCKER AND HIS TEAM
WILL DO THE BEST THEY CAN.

113
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:59,502
I EXPECT YOU TO LEAVE ORBIT
IN TWO DAYS.

114
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:01,588
IF THE PUMPS ARE WORKING, YOU'LL
LEAVE WITH YOUR DEUTERIUM.

115
00:07:01,629 --> 00:07:04,341
IF NOT, YOU'LL LEAVE WITHOUT IT.

116
00:07:04,383 --> 00:07:06,927
ARE WE AGREED?

117
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,597
AGREED.

118
00:07:15,894 --> 00:07:18,188
PHLOX: IT'S YOURS,
IF YOU'D LIKE IT.

119
00:07:18,230 --> 00:07:20,148
I WOULDN'T KNOW
WHAT TO FEED IT.

120
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,358
[ PHLOX CHUCKLES ]

121
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,193
PHLOX: HER NEEDS ARE MODEST--

122
00:07:23,235 --> 00:07:25,570
A NUTRIENT BROTH
EVERY THREE OR FOUR DAYS...

123
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:27,322
LESS OFTEN
WHEN SHE'S WORKING.

124
00:07:27,364 --> 00:07:28,615
WOMAN: WORKING?

125
00:07:28,656 --> 00:07:30,033
SHE'LL INGEST A LITTLE BLOOD

126
00:07:30,075 --> 00:07:32,577
WHILE SHE'S HEALING
AN INJURED ARTERY.

127
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:37,665
THANK YOU, BUT I'LL JUST TAKE
SOME VASCULAR ADHESIVE.

128
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:41,669
PHLOX: UH, TRY THIS,
HMM, INSTEAD?

129
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:46,967
AN AUTO-SUTURE.

130
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:49,844
HMM. I'M SURPRISED
YOU DON'T HAVE ONE.

131
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:53,181
THIS IS A VERY EXPENSIVE
PIECE OF EQUIPMENT. I CAN'T--

132
00:07:53,223 --> 00:07:56,643
PHLOX: NONSENSE. PLEASE.

133
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:03,942
CARDIO-STIMULATOR,
NEURAL-SHOCK KIT. HUH.

134
00:08:03,984 --> 00:08:06,111
I HAD NO IDEA
PROCESSING DEUTERIUM

135
00:08:06,153 --> 00:08:07,904
WAS SUCH A DANGEROUS BUSINESS.

136
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:10,949
IT CAN BE.

137
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:13,701
I'VE, UH, ONLY HEARD
OF HEXATRIOL BEING USED

138
00:08:13,743 --> 00:08:16,496
TO TREAT SERIOUS PLASMA BURNS.

139
00:08:16,537 --> 00:08:19,416
DEUTERIUM CAN BURN
ALMOST AS HOT AS PLASMA

140
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:21,209
WHEN IT'S IGNITED.

141
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:24,504
I HOPE YOU WON'T NEED IT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

142
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:29,968
IS THERE SOMETHING WRONG?

143
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:32,053
NO.

144
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:37,142
I'D BETTER GET BACK.

145
00:08:37,184 --> 00:08:39,227
OF COURSE.

146
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:44,232
THANK YOU AGAIN.

147
00:08:50,738 --> 00:08:52,324
ARCHER: YOU'VE BEEN
TO OTHER COLONIES

148
00:08:52,366 --> 00:08:53,908
THAT TRADE DEUTERIUM,
HAVEN'T YOU?

149
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,952
T'POL: SEVERAL.

150
00:08:55,994 --> 00:08:57,954
ARCHER: ARE THEY ALL
THIS RUSTIC?

151
00:08:57,996 --> 00:08:59,914
T'POL: NOT USUALLY.

152
00:08:59,956 --> 00:09:02,501
ARCHER: THEIR EQUIPMENT'S
FALLING APART.

153
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:04,336
HALF THESE STRUCTURES LOOK LIKE
THEY'RE ABOUT TO COLLAPSE.

154
00:09:04,378 --> 00:09:09,216
PHLOX TELLS ME THEY DON'T EVEN
HAVE BASIC MEDICAL SUPPLIES.

155
00:09:10,717 --> 00:09:14,262
DEUTERIUM IS
A HIGHLY VALUABLE COMMODITY.

156
00:09:14,304 --> 00:09:17,098
YOU'D THINK THESE PEOPLE
WOULD BE BETTER OFF.

157
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:19,059
T'POL: WE'RE HERE
TO TRADE WITH THEM,

158
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:20,601
NOT JUDGE
THEIR LIVING CONDITIONS.

159
00:09:20,643 --> 00:09:22,229
[ ARCHER SIGHS ]

160
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,938
ARCHER: THEN WHY DO THEY NEED US
TO FINISH FIXING THEIR PUMPS

161
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:25,606
IN TWO DAYS?

162
00:09:25,648 --> 00:09:28,318
WHAT'S THE HURRY?

163
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,861
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

164
00:09:29,903 --> 00:09:32,239
MAYWEATHER: LIEUTENANT, A SHIP
JUST DROPPED OUT OF WARP.

165
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:34,824
600,000 KILOMETERS AND CLOSING.

166
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:36,243
I SEE HER.

167
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:39,496
HOSHI: IT'S PROBABLY
MORE DEUTERIUM CUSTOMERS.

168
00:09:39,538 --> 00:09:44,709
I'M READING 12 BIO-SIGNS,
ALL KLINGON.

169
00:09:57,138 --> 00:09:58,765
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

170
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:01,017
TUCKER: YOU'LL WANT TO KEEP
AN EYE ON THOSE PHASE INVERTERS.

171
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:02,185
THEY TEND TO DEPOLARIZE.

172
00:10:02,227 --> 00:10:04,104
[ INTERCOM BUZZING ]

173
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:05,439
SECOND MAN: PUMP SIX.

174
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:07,399
First man: Korok's ship
is entering orbit.

175
00:10:07,441 --> 00:10:09,067
SECOND MAN: I THOUGHT WE HAD
THREE MORE DAYS.

176
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:12,487
First man: Secure the pumps.
Get everyone inside.

177
00:10:12,529 --> 00:10:14,030
TUCKER: SOME KIND OF TROUBLE?

178
00:10:14,072 --> 00:10:16,866
SECOND MAN: HELP ME CLOSE
THESE INDUCTION VALVES.

179
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:24,291
TUCKER: WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHO'S KOROK?

180
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:30,964
THEY MUST REALIZE THAT
YOU TRADE WITH OTHER SHIPS.

181
00:10:31,005 --> 00:10:33,925
FIRST MAN: THEY BELIEVE THAT WE
HAVE AN EXCLUSIVE ARRANGEMENT.

182
00:10:33,967 --> 00:10:35,676
WOMAN: IF THEY THINK ANYONE'S
BEEN HERE BEFORE THEM,

183
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:37,429
THEY GET VERY ANGRY.

184
00:10:37,471 --> 00:10:40,765
FIRST MAN: PLEASE,
DON'T GET INVOLVED.

185
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:44,144
WE'LL TALK TO THEM.

186
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:51,234
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

187
00:10:51,276 --> 00:10:52,486
ARCHER TO<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

188
00:10:52,527 --> 00:10:54,195
Reed: Go ahead, Captain.

189
00:10:54,237 --> 00:10:57,073
HAVE THE KLINGONS
DETECTED<i> ENTERPRISE</i> YET?

190
00:10:58,617 --> 00:11:00,577
NO INDICATION, SIR.

191
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:06,207
ARCHER: TRAVIS,
ADJUST YOUR ORBIT.

192
00:11:06,249 --> 00:11:08,126
KEEP<i> ENTERPRISE</i> OUT OF SIGHT.

193
00:11:08,168 --> 00:11:09,836
AYE, SIR.

194
00:11:35,694 --> 00:11:37,822
KOROK: MY OLD FRIEND.

195
00:11:37,864 --> 00:11:39,658
[ CHUCKLES ]

196
00:11:39,698 --> 00:11:41,993
WE WEREN'T EXPECTING YOU
SO SOON.

197
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:44,245
WE'VE HAD TROUBLE
WITH TWO OF OUR PUMPS.

198
00:11:44,287 --> 00:11:46,914
KOROK: MY CREW'S HUNGRY.

199
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:48,833
LET'S HAVE FOOD AND DRINK.

200
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:51,836
THEN WE'LL DISCUSS BUSINESS.

201
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:56,257
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

202
00:11:57,551 --> 00:12:01,804
YOUR DEUTERIUM--
WE DON'T HAVE ALL OF IT.

203
00:12:01,846 --> 00:12:05,099
WE DID OUR BEST,
BUT WE NEED MORE TIME.

204
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:12,148
TUCKER: CAN YOU MAKE OUT
WHAT THEY'RE SAYING?

205
00:12:12,190 --> 00:12:14,150
T'POL: TESSIC IS EXPLAINING
THAT THEIR YIELD

206
00:12:14,192 --> 00:12:17,237
ISN'T WHAT THEY'D HOPED.

207
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:19,072
TUCKER: GOOD EARS.

208
00:12:19,113 --> 00:12:20,739
TESSIC: ...MAKE ANY DIFFERENCE.

209
00:12:20,781 --> 00:12:24,202
WITHOUT THOSE PUMPS, WE COULDN'T
OPERATE AT FULL CAPACITY.

210
00:12:24,244 --> 00:12:27,163
I SENSE WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO SAY

211
00:12:27,205 --> 00:12:30,917
IS NOT GOING TO MAKE ME HAPPY.

212
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:34,295
WE CAN GIVE YOU
80,000 LITERS.

213
00:12:34,337 --> 00:12:36,423
IF YOU'LL GIVE US ONE MORE WEEK,
WE'LL HAVE THE REST.

214
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,383
KOROK: YOU'VE HAD ENOUGH TIME.

215
00:12:38,425 --> 00:12:40,594
WE'LL TAKE ALL OF IT, NOW!

216
00:12:40,635 --> 00:12:42,596
WE DON'T HAVE IT.

217
00:12:42,637 --> 00:12:44,472
I TOLD YOU, TWO PUMPS WERE DOWN.

218
00:12:44,514 --> 00:12:47,559
KOROK: THEY ALL
APPEAR TO BE WORKING.

219
00:12:47,601 --> 00:12:49,936
WE WERE JUST ABLE
TO REPAIR THEM.

220
00:12:49,977 --> 00:12:52,021
-YOU'RE LYING!
-UGH!

221
00:12:52,063 --> 00:12:53,772
SECOND MAN: LEAVE HIM ALONE.

222
00:12:53,814 --> 00:12:55,774
YOU'LL GET YOUR DEUTERIUM.

223
00:12:55,816 --> 00:12:57,736
UGH!

224
00:13:00,447 --> 00:13:02,616
TESSIC: WAIT, PLEASE.

225
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:09,997
I CAN GET DEUTERIUM ANYWHERE.

226
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:13,585
I COME HERE
BECAUSE I LIKE YOU...

227
00:13:13,627 --> 00:13:17,880
WHEN YOU SHOW ME
HOSPITALITY AND RESPECT.

228
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:20,508
SECOND MAN: YOU TAKE
EVERYTHING WE OWN,

229
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:23,010
AND YOU WANT US TO RESPECT YOU.

230
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:31,018
I'LL GIVE YOU FOUR DAYS.

231
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:33,688
HAVE IT ALL READY.

232
00:13:33,730 --> 00:13:35,982
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

233
00:13:48,995 --> 00:13:51,080
WOMAN: LET'S GET HIM INSIDE.

234
00:14:08,515 --> 00:14:10,099
ARCHER: SO THIS IS YOUR
EXCLUSIVE ARRANGEMENT?

235
00:14:10,141 --> 00:14:11,768
TESSIC: IT'S NOT YOUR CONCERN.

236
00:14:11,810 --> 00:14:14,604
TUCKER: HOW LONG HAVE THESE
BULLIES BEEN PUSHING YOU AROUND?

237
00:14:14,646 --> 00:14:16,189
SECOND MAN: FIVE SEASONS.

238
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:18,566
THEY TAKE ALL THE FIRST-YIELD
DEUTERIUM WE CAN EXTRACT.

239
00:14:18,608 --> 00:14:20,360
WOMAN: HOLD STILL.

240
00:14:20,401 --> 00:14:22,028
SECOND MAN: AFTER THEY LEAVE,

241
00:14:22,069 --> 00:14:24,447
WE MANAGE TO PULL A FEW THOUSAND
LITERS OUT OF THE DEEP STRATA,

242
00:14:24,489 --> 00:14:26,574
BUT IT TAKES WEEKS,
AND IT'S SO FULL OF IMPURITIES

243
00:14:26,616 --> 00:14:27,950
WE CAN BARELY REFINE IT.

244
00:14:27,992 --> 00:14:29,577
TESSIC: IT STILL BRINGS IN
A DECENT PRICE.

245
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:31,245
WE MAKE ENOUGH TO GET
THROUGH THE WINTER.

246
00:14:31,287 --> 00:14:32,955
SECOND MAN: BARELY.

247
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:34,791
T'POL: HAVE YOU TRIED CONTACTING
YOUR HOMEWORLD?

248
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,459
IT'S TOO FAR AWAY.

249
00:14:36,501 --> 00:14:40,254
TUCKER: YOU MUST HAVE WEAPONS,
SOME WAY TO DEFEND YOURSELVES.

250
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:41,715
HOW MANY OF THEM ARE THERE?

251
00:14:41,756 --> 00:14:45,134
USUALLY SEVEN.

252
00:14:45,176 --> 00:14:47,679
TUCKER: SEVEN?

253
00:14:47,721 --> 00:14:50,807
YOU'VE GOT THEM OUTNUMBERED
NINE OR TEN TO ONE.

254
00:14:50,849 --> 00:14:54,769
TESSIC: YOU'VE NEVER SEEN
A KLINGON IN BATTLE, HAVE YOU?

255
00:14:54,811 --> 00:14:59,315
WE TRIED TO STAND UP TO THEM
ONCE, THREE SEASONS AGO.

256
00:14:59,357 --> 00:15:01,901
FIVE OF US DIED FIGHTING THEM.

257
00:15:01,942 --> 00:15:06,906
AND THEN THEY KILLED THREE MORE
TO PROVE THEIR POINT.

258
00:15:06,947 --> 00:15:09,909
ONE OF THEM WAS HIS FATHER.

259
00:15:12,662 --> 00:15:15,164
ARCHER: MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING
WE CAN DO.

260
00:15:18,376 --> 00:15:20,420
JUST TAKE YOUR 200 LITERS
AND GO.

261
00:15:20,461 --> 00:15:24,465
IF YOU'RE HERE WHEN THEY
COME BACK, THEY'LL KILL YOU.

262
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,427
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

263
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:28,762
ARCHER: MR. REED?

264
00:15:28,803 --> 00:15:30,597
Reed: The Klingon ship's
gone to warp, sir.

265
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:32,348
I'm sending a shuttlepod down.

266
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:35,309
ARCHER: WE'LL BE AT
THE LANDING SITE.

267
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:37,937
MAN: THE PRESSURE'S STEADY
AT 8.07.

268
00:15:37,978 --> 00:15:40,940
CHECK UP AT THE TOP.

269
00:15:52,993 --> 00:15:55,747
TUCKER: I'LL CATCH UP WITH YOU
LATER, CAPTAIN.

270
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:10,511
SORRY I NEVER GOT
TO GIVE YOU THAT TOUR.

271
00:16:10,553 --> 00:16:14,014
I ONCE SAW A KELLENITE SHIP
WITH CANNONS AND TORPEDOES.

272
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:17,184
YEAH. MOST BIG SHIPS
CARRY WEAPONS.

273
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:19,938
LIKE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

274
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:24,108
YEAH, LIKE<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

275
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:27,946
YOU COULD HAVE FOUGHT
THE KLINGONS, BEATEN THEM.

276
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:32,199
MAYBE.

277
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:34,452
WHY DIDN'T YOU TRY?

278
00:16:34,494 --> 00:16:36,203
[ SIGHS ]

279
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:38,456
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

280
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:46,589
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

281
00:16:46,631 --> 00:16:48,508
COME IN.

282
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:55,974
T'POL: THE DEUTERIUM'S
BEEN STOWED--200 LITERS.

283
00:16:59,519 --> 00:17:01,437
SHOULD I INSTRUCT
ENSIGN MAYWEATHER

284
00:17:01,479 --> 00:17:03,523
TO BREAK ORBIT?

285
00:17:04,774 --> 00:17:07,401
ARCHER: SO THAT'S IT?

286
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:10,279
WE JUST TAKE OUR DEUTERIUM
AND LEAVE?

287
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:17,453
THEY WORK THEIR ASSES OFF
TO PROVIDE FOR THEIR FAMILIES,

288
00:17:17,495 --> 00:17:20,080
AND THEN THE KLINGONS JUST
STROLL IN AND ROB THEM BLIND.

289
00:17:20,122 --> 00:17:22,500
DOES THAT SEEM RIGHT TO YOU?

290
00:17:22,542 --> 00:17:25,378
MALCOLM TELLS ME
THAT KLINGON SHIP

291
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:28,047
ISN'T MUCH MORE
THAN A FREIGHTER.

292
00:17:28,088 --> 00:17:30,633
I'D LAY ODDS THEY'RE
NO MATCH FOR<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

293
00:17:30,675 --> 00:17:33,011
AND IF THEY WITHDRAW?

294
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:36,180
WHAT WILL KEEP THEM FROM COMING
BACK AFTER WE'VE GONE?

295
00:17:38,808 --> 00:17:42,395
WE COULD TRY TO CONTACT
THE KLINGON HIGH COUNCIL.

296
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:45,523
WE SAVED KLAANG
FROM THE SULIBAN.

297
00:17:45,565 --> 00:17:49,360
WE PULLED ONE OF THEIR BATTLE
CRUISERS OUT OF A GAS GIANT.

298
00:17:49,402 --> 00:17:52,780
I SAY THEY OWE US A FAVOR.

299
00:17:52,822 --> 00:17:56,116
I DOUBT THESE MARAUDERS
ANSWER TO THE HIGH COUNCIL.

300
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:58,118
I ALREADY KNOW
WHERE VULCANS STAND

301
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,662
ON INTERFERING
WITH OTHER CULTURES,

302
00:17:59,704 --> 00:18:01,581
BUT THIS ISN'T A CULTURE.

303
00:18:01,622 --> 00:18:04,625
76 SETTLERS
ARE BEING PREYED UPON.

304
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:06,168
IF THIS WERE AN EARTH COLONY,

305
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:09,380
I'D BE GRATEFUL IF SOMEONE
SHOWED UP TO GIVE ME A HAND.

306
00:18:11,925 --> 00:18:15,887
CAPTAIN, THIS MAY SURPRISE YOU,
BUT I AGREE.

307
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:19,933
HOWEVER,
SHORT OF KILLING THE KLINGONS,

308
00:18:19,974 --> 00:18:23,978
ANY ACTION WE TAKE WILL ONLY
MAKE THE SITUATION WORSE.

309
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:30,735
I JUST HATE THE IDEA
OF TURNING OUR BACKS.

310
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:46,751
[ TESSIC GRUNTS ]

311
00:18:46,793 --> 00:18:48,962
ARCHER: NEED A HAND?

312
00:18:51,589 --> 00:18:53,841
TESSIC: CONTROL ARM IS JAMMED.

313
00:18:53,883 --> 00:18:56,594
I COULD USE SOME HELP
WITH THE RELEASE VALVE.

314
00:18:56,636 --> 00:18:58,638
ARCHER: OK.

315
00:18:58,679 --> 00:19:01,140
TESSIC: TURN IT TO THE LEFT.

316
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:07,063
ARCHER: THIS ONE?

317
00:19:10,316 --> 00:19:12,234
TESSIC: THOUGHT YOU'D BE OFF
CHARTING YOUR NEXT STAR SYSTEM

318
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:14,612
BY NOW.

319
00:19:14,654 --> 00:19:18,032
ARCHER: SOMETIMES I HAVE A BAD
HABIT OF OVERSTAYING MY WELCOME.

320
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:20,994
WELL, YOU OBVIOUSLY
DIDN'T COME DOWN HERE

321
00:19:21,035 --> 00:19:24,163
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT
TO HELP ME WITH THIS CRAWLER.

322
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:28,918
ARCHER: SEEMS TO ME THIS CRAWLER
IS THE LEAST OF YOUR PROBLEMS.

323
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,878
TESSIC: WE'VE BEEN
THROUGH THIS BEFORE.

324
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,922
IT'S NOT YOUR CONCERN.

325
00:19:35,215 --> 00:19:37,885
GIVE IT ANOTHER TURN.

326
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:43,557
YOU SAID THEY'VE BEEN
COMING HERE FOR, WHAT,

327
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:46,352
FIVE SEASONS?

328
00:19:46,393 --> 00:19:48,146
HOW MUCH LONGER DO YOU PLAN
ON LETTING THIS GO ON,

329
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:49,271
ANOTHER FIVE?

330
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:51,649
THAT'S GOOD.
LEAVE IT THERE.

331
00:19:56,654 --> 00:19:59,782
TESSIC: RECONNECT
THIS COOLANT LINE.

332
00:19:59,824 --> 00:20:02,660
THE INTAKE'S ABOVE YOUR HEAD.

333
00:20:12,086 --> 00:20:15,422
I HAD A TALK WITH
MY TACTICAL OFFICER.

334
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:19,093
WE'RE CONFIDENT YOU HAVE THE
ABILITY TO DEFEND YOURSELVES.

335
00:20:19,135 --> 00:20:20,970
WE ALREADY TRIED.

336
00:20:21,012 --> 00:20:22,889
THERE ARE EIGHT PEOPLE
BURIED NOT FAR FROM HERE

337
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:24,598
WHO CAN ATTEST TO THAT.

338
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:27,143
IT WOULD BE DIFFERENT THIS TIME.

339
00:20:27,185 --> 00:20:28,686
WE WOULD HELP YOU PREPARE.

340
00:20:28,728 --> 00:20:29,937
I DON'T WANT YOUR HELP.

341
00:20:29,979 --> 00:20:31,522
I'M RESPONSIBLE FOR MY PEOPLE,
NOT YOU.

342
00:20:31,564 --> 00:20:33,566
THEY PUT THEIR TRUST IN ME.
THEY DEPEND ON ME.

343
00:20:33,607 --> 00:20:35,860
I'M SUPPOSED TO PROTECT THEM!

344
00:20:41,074 --> 00:20:43,201
TESSIC: LOOK AT ME.

345
00:20:44,577 --> 00:20:47,413
I CAN BARELY KEEP
THIS CRAWLER RUNNING.

346
00:20:52,168 --> 00:20:55,922
YOU SAY YOU AND YOUR TACTICAL
OFFICER WANT TO HELP US.

347
00:20:55,963 --> 00:20:59,967
EVEN IF YOU DO, ONCE YOU'RE
GONE, WE'LL BE ALONE AGAIN,

348
00:21:00,009 --> 00:21:02,428
WAITING FOR THEM TO COME BACK.

349
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:08,601
THERE'S A SAYING ON MY WORLD.

350
00:21:11,562 --> 00:21:16,525
GIVE A MAN A FISH,
AND HE EATS FOR A DAY;

351
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:21,572
TEACH HIM TO FISH,
AND HE EATS FOR A LIFETIME.

352
00:21:29,747 --> 00:21:32,291
REED: I WAS HOPING FOR
A BIT MORE TO WORK WITH.

353
00:21:32,332 --> 00:21:34,418
SECOND MAN: THEY DO A DECENT JOB
KEEPING THE  SHIB'A LIZARDS

354
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:36,295
FROM CHEWING ON
THE POWER COUPLINGS.

355
00:21:36,336 --> 00:21:38,422
WITH A FEW MODIFICATIONS,

356
00:21:38,464 --> 00:21:40,883
THESE SHOULD BE EFFECTIVE
AGAINST MORE THAN LIZARDS.

357
00:21:40,925 --> 00:21:44,137
YOU MUST HAVE A WELL-STOCKED
ARMORY ONBOARD<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

358
00:21:44,178 --> 00:21:47,014
BUT THIS BATTLE
WON'T BE WON WITH FIREPOWER.

359
00:21:47,056 --> 00:21:50,517
DECEPTION AND SURPRISE CAN BE
JUST AS POTENT AS BRUTE FORCE.

360
00:21:50,559 --> 00:21:53,312
KLINGONS ARE
AGGRESSIVE WARRIORS,

361
00:21:53,353 --> 00:21:55,564
BUT THEIR TACTICS ARE CRUDE.

362
00:21:55,606 --> 00:21:58,776
THEY'RE SLOW TO ADAPT
TO CHANGING CIRCUMSTANCES.

363
00:21:58,818 --> 00:22:01,946
TESSIC: THIS ALL SOUNDS
VERY AMBITIOUS.

364
00:22:01,988 --> 00:22:04,198
WHAT EXACTLY ARE YOU
EXPECTING US TO DO?

365
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:07,576
ARCHER: YOU'RE GOING
TO LURE THEM INTO A TRAP.

366
00:22:07,618 --> 00:22:09,411
WHAT KIND OF TRAP?

367
00:22:09,453 --> 00:22:11,455
TUCKER: A VERY HOT ONE.

368
00:22:11,497 --> 00:22:13,373
THE DEUTERIUM
IN THOSE WELLHEADS--

369
00:22:13,415 --> 00:22:16,252
HOW MUCH PRESSURE IS IT UNDER,
3,000, 4,000 MILLIBARS?

370
00:22:16,294 --> 00:22:17,670
5,000.

371
00:22:17,711 --> 00:22:20,422
TUCKER: SHOULD CREATE
SOME INTERESTING FIREWORKS.

372
00:22:20,464 --> 00:22:22,216
TESSIC: YOU'LL NEVER
GET THE KLINGONS NEAR

373
00:22:22,258 --> 00:22:23,717
THAT DEUTERIUM FIELD.

374
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:25,469
THEY KNOW IT ISN'T SAFE.

375
00:22:25,511 --> 00:22:27,554
SECOND MAN: THEY MAY BE CRUDE,
BUT THEY'RE NOT FOOLS.

376
00:22:27,596 --> 00:22:30,308
THAT'S WHERE DECEPTION
AND SURPRISE COME IN.

377
00:22:30,348 --> 00:22:32,643
DID YOU BRING THE MAP
I ASKED YOU FOR?

378
00:22:32,685 --> 00:22:34,478
TESSIC: IT'S RIGHT HERE.

379
00:22:38,356 --> 00:22:39,775
ARCHER: THE STRUCTURES
IN THE COLONY--

380
00:22:39,817 --> 00:22:41,319
THEY'RE MOSTLY MODULAR, RIGHT?

381
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:42,945
THEY'RE ALL MODULAR.

382
00:22:42,987 --> 00:22:44,613
MOST DEUTERIUM FIELDS
ARE DEPLETED

383
00:22:44,655 --> 00:22:46,448
WITHIN THREE OR FOUR YEARS
AT MOST,

384
00:22:46,490 --> 00:22:48,659
FORCES US TO BE ITINERANT.

385
00:22:48,701 --> 00:22:51,329
SO YOU'RE SAYING YOU COULD
RELOCATE THESE BUILDINGS

386
00:22:51,369 --> 00:22:53,371
IN A RELATIVELY SHORT TIME?

387
00:22:53,413 --> 00:22:54,665
SECOND MAN: IT DEPENDS.

388
00:22:54,707 --> 00:22:56,458
WHERE ARE YOU SUGGESTING
WE RELOCATE THEM?

389
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:59,170
ARCHER: ABOUT 50 METERS
TO THE SOUTH, RIGHT HERE.

390
00:22:59,212 --> 00:23:00,838
WHAT GOOD WOULD THAT DO?

391
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,340
THE TERRAIN THERE
IS NO DIFFERENT

392
00:23:02,380 --> 00:23:03,674
THAN WHERE THE TOWN IS NOW.

393
00:23:03,716 --> 00:23:05,425
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE COUNTING ON.

394
00:23:05,467 --> 00:23:07,887
IF WE CAN MOVE
THE STRUCTURES AND THE RIGS,

395
00:23:07,928 --> 00:23:10,973
EVERYTHING SHOULD LOOK PRETTY
MUCH LIKE IT DID YESTERDAY.

396
00:23:11,015 --> 00:23:13,934
EVERYTHING EXCEPT THE WELLHEADS.

397
00:23:13,976 --> 00:23:18,022
THEY'LL HAVE TO BE
CAPPED OFF AND CAMOUFLAGED.

398
00:23:18,064 --> 00:23:21,275
WE CAN DO THAT.

399
00:23:21,317 --> 00:23:24,444
REED: THE GULLIES
ON THIS HILLSIDE--

400
00:23:24,486 --> 00:23:25,905
ARE THEY DEEP ENOUGH TO HIDE IN?

401
00:23:25,946 --> 00:23:28,657
IF YOU KEEP YOUR HEAD DOWN.

402
00:23:28,699 --> 00:23:31,285
T'POL: WE'LL SHUTTLE
SMALL GROUPS TO<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

403
00:23:31,327 --> 00:23:33,495
FOR WHATEVER TRAINING
WE HAVE TIME FOR,

404
00:23:33,537 --> 00:23:37,041
PREFERABLY PEOPLE WHO HAVE
EXPERIENCE WITH WEAPONS.

405
00:23:38,251 --> 00:23:40,044
ARCHER: WE'VE GOT THREE DAYS.

406
00:23:40,086 --> 00:23:42,129
WE SHOULD GET TO WORK.

407
00:23:44,006 --> 00:23:46,424
TESSIC: WHAT ARE WE WAITING FOR?

408
00:23:54,392 --> 00:23:57,395
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

409
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:18,624
TUCKER: ONE MORE METER.

410
00:24:19,708 --> 00:24:22,420
OK, SHUT HER DOWN.

411
00:24:24,046 --> 00:24:26,299
REED: YOU READY?

412
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:31,220
[ COMPUTER BEEPING ]

413
00:24:31,262 --> 00:24:33,555
REED: AND BEGIN.

414
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:48,862
SECOND MAN: SHIB'A LIZARDS
DON'T MOVE THAT FAST.

415
00:24:48,904 --> 00:24:51,073
HOSHI: DO YOU MIND, LIEUTENANT?

416
00:24:51,115 --> 00:24:52,908
REED: UH-UH.

417
00:24:52,950 --> 00:24:54,410
HOSHI: I CAN SEE YOUR FINGER
TENSING ON THE TRIGGER

418
00:24:54,452 --> 00:24:55,493
BEFORE YOU FIRE.

419
00:24:55,535 --> 00:24:57,495
IT'S THROWING OFF YOUR AIM.

420
00:24:57,537 --> 00:25:00,124
I USED TO MAKE THE SAME MISTAKE.

421
00:25:00,166 --> 00:25:02,001
KEEP YOUR EYE ON THE TARGET,

422
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:05,421
AND DON'T SQUEEZE THE TRIGGER
UNTIL YOU HAVE A CLEAR SHOT.

423
00:25:09,967 --> 00:25:11,969
HOSHI: TRY AGAIN.

424
00:25:22,104 --> 00:25:24,357
TUCKER: I THINK THE TABLE
WAS A LITTLE BIT TO THE LEFT.

425
00:25:24,398 --> 00:25:27,776
ARCHER: HEH. THANKS.

426
00:25:27,818 --> 00:25:29,487
HOW ARE THINGS GOING
WITH THE PUMPS?

427
00:25:29,527 --> 00:25:31,989
TUCKER: AH, IT'LL BE TOMORROW
BEFORE THEY'RE ALL IN PLACE.

428
00:25:32,031 --> 00:25:35,493
WE'VE STARTED
CAPPING OFF THE HEADS.

429
00:25:35,533 --> 00:25:38,704
ARCHER: LET ME KNOW--I GOT IT.

430
00:25:38,745 --> 00:25:41,539
THANKS--
IF YOU NEED MORE PEOPLE.

431
00:25:41,581 --> 00:25:43,501
I RIGGED TWO IGNITION SEQUENCES.

432
00:25:43,541 --> 00:25:47,087
THE PERIMETER AND THE CENTER
ARE ON SEPARATE CIRCUITS.

433
00:25:47,129 --> 00:25:50,132
TUCKER: I THOUGHT TAKING
THE TOWN APART WAS TOUGH.

434
00:25:51,675 --> 00:25:53,760
BUT PUTTING IT BACK TOGETHER...

435
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:57,555
THIS PLAN IS A LONG SHOT,
ISN'T IT?

436
00:26:01,435 --> 00:26:02,769
YOU THINK IT'S A MISTAKE?

437
00:26:02,811 --> 00:26:05,772
I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

438
00:26:10,319 --> 00:26:12,696
I'VE NEVER LIKED BULLIES,
TRIP--

439
00:26:12,738 --> 00:26:16,283
NOT ON EARTH,
AND NOT OUT HERE.

440
00:26:19,495 --> 00:26:22,580
T'POL: KLINGONS
CARRY DISRUPTERS,

441
00:26:22,622 --> 00:26:26,752
BUT THEY PREFER TO USE
BLADED WEAPONS IN COMBAT,

442
00:26:26,793 --> 00:26:30,839
THE TWO MOST COMMON
BEING THE BAT'LETH,

443
00:26:30,881 --> 00:26:33,759
A CURVED, BILATERAL SWORD,

444
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:38,638
AND THE MEK'LETH,
A TWO-PRONGED DAGGER.

445
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:40,349
THE BAT'LETH

446
00:26:40,391 --> 00:26:43,727
CAN DECAPITATE ITS VICTIM
WITH ONE STROKE,

447
00:26:43,769 --> 00:26:46,813
WHILE THE MEK'LETH
IS TYPICALLY USED

448
00:26:46,855 --> 00:26:51,527
TO SLASH THE THROAT
OR DISEMBOWEL.

449
00:26:53,737 --> 00:26:55,739
I CANNOT TEACH YOU
TO DEFEND YOURSELVES

450
00:26:55,781 --> 00:26:58,242
AGAINST THESE WEAPONS.

451
00:26:58,284 --> 00:27:01,495
THE VULCAN MARTIAL ART,
SUUS MAHNA,

452
00:27:01,537 --> 00:27:03,747
TAKES YEARS TO MASTER.

453
00:27:03,789 --> 00:27:08,961
HOWEVER, I CAN TEACH YOU
A SIMPLE EVASIVE TECHNIQUE.

454
00:27:09,002 --> 00:27:10,963
ENSIGN MAYWEATHER.

455
00:27:11,004 --> 00:27:13,215
SINCE I DON'T
HAVE A BAT'LETH,

456
00:27:13,257 --> 00:27:16,385
THIS WILL HAVE TO SUFFICE.

457
00:27:16,427 --> 00:27:18,429
TRY TO STRIKE ME.

458
00:27:21,390 --> 00:27:23,100
YOU WON'T HURT ME.

459
00:27:23,142 --> 00:27:26,228
MAYWEATHER: IT'S NOT YOU
THAT I'M WORRIED ABOUT.

460
00:27:33,611 --> 00:27:35,946
THAT WAS CALLED
THE NAVORKOT.

461
00:27:35,988 --> 00:27:39,283
IT ISN'T DIFFICULT TO LEARN.

462
00:27:39,325 --> 00:27:41,994
WHO WOULD LIKE TO TRY FIRST?

463
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:51,629
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

464
00:28:02,264 --> 00:28:04,391
TUCKER: THANKS.

465
00:28:09,146 --> 00:28:11,315
Q'ELL: LIEUTENANT REED SAID
I'D HAVE TO HIDE IN THE CANYONS

466
00:28:11,357 --> 00:28:12,690
WHEN THE KLINGONS COME BACK.

467
00:28:12,732 --> 00:28:15,361
UH-HUH. HE DOESN'T WANT YOU
TO GET HURT.

468
00:28:18,197 --> 00:28:19,823
BUT I WANT TO HELP.

469
00:28:19,865 --> 00:28:22,826
I CAN SHOOT A SHIB'A LIZARD
FROM 40 METERS.

470
00:28:24,370 --> 00:28:26,497
MALCOLM'S GOT THIS RULE--

471
00:28:26,539 --> 00:28:30,834
YOU'VE GOT TO BE TALLER
THAN THE GUN TO USE IT.

472
00:28:30,876 --> 00:28:32,503
I DON'T WANT TO HIDE.

473
00:28:32,545 --> 00:28:33,962
[ SIGHS ]

474
00:28:34,004 --> 00:28:36,632
WELL...SHOOTING AT A LIZARD
IS A WHOLE LOT DIFFERENT

475
00:28:36,674 --> 00:28:38,592
THAN SHOOTING AT A PERSON.

476
00:28:38,634 --> 00:28:42,596
AND, UH...
LIZARDS DON'T SHOOT BACK.

477
00:28:45,932 --> 00:28:48,310
WHEN THOSE KLINGONS SHOW UP,

478
00:28:48,352 --> 00:28:51,438
I WANT YOU TO DO EXACTLY
WHAT LIEUTENANT REED SAYS.

479
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:53,399
UNDERSTOOD?

480
00:28:54,358 --> 00:28:56,109
YES, SIR.

481
00:28:58,153 --> 00:29:00,906
[ TARGETS BEEPING ]

482
00:29:43,282 --> 00:29:46,535
ARCHER: WE HAD A LITTLE TROUBLE
MOVING ONE OF THE PUMPS,

483
00:29:46,577 --> 00:29:49,413
BUT IT'S IN PLACE NOW.

484
00:29:49,455 --> 00:29:51,790
WE'RE READY.

485
00:29:53,375 --> 00:29:55,835
I JUST HOPE EVERYONE
SURVIVES THIS.

486
00:29:58,631 --> 00:30:01,550
YOUR PEOPLE AS WELL AS MINE.

487
00:30:03,636 --> 00:30:07,973
WE LEFT EARTH
JUST OVER A YEAR AGO

488
00:30:08,014 --> 00:30:12,603
TO EXPLORE,
TO MEET PEOPLE LIKE YOU.

489
00:30:15,522 --> 00:30:17,399
WE'D ONLY BEEN OUT
OF SPACEDOCK FOR THREE DAYS

490
00:30:17,441 --> 00:30:20,235
WHEN WE FOUND OURSELVES

491
00:30:20,277 --> 00:30:23,489
IN A FULL-FLEDGED FIREFIGHT

492
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:27,451
WITH SOME PRETTY NASTY
CHARACTERS CALLED THE SULIBAN.

493
00:30:27,493 --> 00:30:29,035
I GOT SHOT IN THE LEG.

494
00:30:29,077 --> 00:30:33,332
JUST BEFORE I PASSED OUT,
I REMEMBERED THINKING,

495
00:30:33,373 --> 00:30:35,959
"THIS ISN'T
WHAT I SIGNED UP FOR.

496
00:30:36,001 --> 00:30:38,504
"I SHOULD BE MAPPING
STAR CLUSTERS

497
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:42,758
OR MAKING FIRST CONTACT
WITH FRIENDLY SPECIES."

498
00:30:44,718 --> 00:30:46,512
BUT WHEN THOSE SULIBAN

499
00:30:46,553 --> 00:30:50,766
STARTED FIRING AT MY CREW,

500
00:30:50,808 --> 00:30:53,727
I KNEW I DIDN'T HAVE ANY CHOICE

501
00:30:53,769 --> 00:30:56,647
BUT TO FIGHT BACK.

502
00:30:56,689 --> 00:30:59,525
I'M NOT ASHAMED TO ADMIT
I WAS NERVOUS--

503
00:30:59,566 --> 00:31:03,111
I'M NERVOUS NOW--

504
00:31:03,153 --> 00:31:08,033
BUT I KNOW WE CAN DO THIS.

505
00:31:11,036 --> 00:31:13,121
[ COMMUNICATOR BEEPS ]

506
00:31:18,585 --> 00:31:20,086
ARCHER: ARCHER.

507
00:31:20,128 --> 00:31:21,963
Mayweather: The Klingon ship
just dropped out of warp,

508
00:31:22,005 --> 00:31:24,257
Captain.

509
00:31:31,724 --> 00:31:34,184
ACKNOWLEDGED.

510
00:32:13,014 --> 00:32:15,851
LISTEN.

511
00:32:15,893 --> 00:32:18,437
KLINGON: WHAT?

512
00:32:18,478 --> 00:32:21,273
KOROK: THE PUMPS.

513
00:32:21,314 --> 00:32:24,067
THEY'RE SILENT.

514
00:32:27,863 --> 00:32:30,783
WHERE'S YOUR HOSPITALITY?

515
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:37,539
THIS IS NO WAY TO TREAT
YOUR FRIENDS!

516
00:32:37,581 --> 00:32:39,875
[ WEAPON FIRES ]

517
00:32:39,917 --> 00:32:43,128
SHOW YOURSELVES!

518
00:32:47,006 --> 00:32:49,927
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

519
00:33:17,955 --> 00:33:20,791
[ MAN TRILLING ]

520
00:33:22,835 --> 00:33:24,753
KLINGON: HALT!

521
00:33:28,715 --> 00:33:30,258
AGH!

522
00:33:31,134 --> 00:33:33,846
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

523
00:33:35,597 --> 00:33:38,057
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

524
00:33:44,230 --> 00:33:47,317
THIS WILL COST YOU
MORE THAN DEUTERIUM!

525
00:33:51,446 --> 00:33:53,991
[ SHOUTING IN KLINGON ]

526
00:33:56,910 --> 00:33:59,997
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

527
00:34:30,944 --> 00:34:33,030
ARCHER: AHEM.

528
00:34:55,802 --> 00:34:57,554
T'POL: HEY!

529
00:35:17,407 --> 00:35:19,451
T'POL: COME ON.

530
00:35:32,798 --> 00:35:34,591
KLINGON: THERE.

531
00:35:36,426 --> 00:35:38,804
KOROK: WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

532
00:35:38,845 --> 00:35:40,263
YOU'LL KILL US ALL.

533
00:35:40,305 --> 00:35:43,141
THOSE WELLHEADS--
THEY'RE UNDER GREAT PRESSURE.

534
00:35:43,182 --> 00:35:44,517
IF YOU IGNITE THEM,

535
00:35:44,559 --> 00:35:46,061
YOU'LL INCINERATE
THE WHOLE TOWN.

536
00:35:46,103 --> 00:35:49,106
KLINGON: THEY'RE MAKING FOOLS
OF US.

537
00:36:02,327 --> 00:36:05,956
KOROK: THEY'RE HIDING
IN THE DIRT LIKE TARG.

538
00:36:05,998 --> 00:36:08,750
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

539
00:36:08,792 --> 00:36:11,169
THEY'LL LEARN
TO SHOW US RESPECT.

540
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:13,922
WE'LL KILL ANOTHER FOUR...

541
00:36:13,964 --> 00:36:16,591
PERHAPS THE BOY AS WELL.

542
00:36:23,765 --> 00:36:25,558
CAPTAIN.

543
00:36:38,279 --> 00:36:39,906
THEY'RE TOO FAR SOUTH.

544
00:36:39,948 --> 00:36:44,243
AH. WE'VE GOT TO GET THEM TO
MOVE 50 METERS TO OUR LEFT.

545
00:36:44,285 --> 00:36:47,413
EVERYBODY, THIS WAY.

546
00:36:53,962 --> 00:36:57,174
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

547
00:37:14,107 --> 00:37:16,442
REED: A LITTLE FARTHER.

548
00:37:26,078 --> 00:37:27,704
THIS IS GOOD.

549
00:37:43,011 --> 00:37:44,888
A FEW MORE METERS.

550
00:37:49,935 --> 00:37:51,644
[ CLANG ]

551
00:38:03,198 --> 00:38:05,658
THIS SHOULDN'T BE HERE.

552
00:38:05,700 --> 00:38:07,410
ARCHER: NOW.

553
00:38:23,509 --> 00:38:25,971
ARCHER: THEY'RE ALL YOURS,
TESSIC.

554
00:38:32,769 --> 00:38:34,271
KOROK!

555
00:38:36,148 --> 00:38:38,024
I WOULDN'T DO THAT!

556
00:38:38,066 --> 00:38:41,820
THERE'S TWO MORE WELLHEADS
BY YOUR FEET!

557
00:38:41,861 --> 00:38:44,072
LEAVE HERE NOW
OR WE'LL IGNITE THEM!

558
00:38:44,114 --> 00:38:46,241
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

559
00:38:46,283 --> 00:38:47,993
YOU'LL LIVE TO REGRET THIS.

560
00:38:48,034 --> 00:38:52,038
IF YOU'RE THINKING ABOUT COMING
BACK, I WOULDN'T ADVISE IT.

561
00:38:53,748 --> 00:38:55,792
WE'LL BE READY.

562
00:38:57,669 --> 00:39:00,338
WE'RE NOT AFRAID OF YOU ANYMORE.

563
00:39:05,426 --> 00:39:07,512
WE CAN FIND DEUTERIUM ANYWHERE.

564
00:39:07,553 --> 00:39:09,806
YOURS ISN'T FIT
FOR A GARBAGE SCOW.

565
00:39:09,848 --> 00:39:12,184
[ SPEAKING KLINGON ]

566
00:39:24,112 --> 00:39:26,948
[ CHEERING ]

567
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:57,937
TUCKER: UNLESS YOU'RE PLANNING
TO JOIN STARFLEET,

568
00:39:57,979 --> 00:40:01,233
I'M AFRAID YOU'LL HAVE
TO GIVE UP THAT CHAIR.

569
00:40:04,194 --> 00:40:05,862
I WISH YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO LEAVE.

570
00:40:05,904 --> 00:40:09,866
YEAH, THAT'S ONE OF THE TOUGH
THINGS ABOUT MY JOB--

571
00:40:09,908 --> 00:40:13,870
SAYING GOODBYE TO PEOPLE
LIKE YOU AND YOUR FRIENDS.

572
00:40:15,914 --> 00:40:18,917
OH. ALMOST FORGOT.

573
00:40:25,006 --> 00:40:27,675
SCHEMATICS FOR<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

574
00:40:27,717 --> 00:40:30,469
YOU SAID YOU LIKE
TO LOOK AT STARSHIPS.

575
00:40:31,804 --> 00:40:34,140
THIS ONE'LL KNOCK
YOUR SOCKS OFF.

576
00:40:34,182 --> 00:40:36,434
THANKS.

577
00:40:39,187 --> 00:40:41,064
DO YOU THINK YOU'LL COME BACK?

578
00:40:42,523 --> 00:40:44,943
[ SIGHS ]

579
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:46,652
WHO KNOWS?

580
00:40:46,694 --> 00:40:49,155
OUR ENGINES
NEED A LOT OF DEUTERIUM.

581
00:40:49,197 --> 00:40:52,617
ARCHER: THERE MUST BE
OVER 1,000 LITERS HERE.

582
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:54,452
SECOND MAN: 2,000.

583
00:40:54,493 --> 00:40:56,204
ARCHER: OUR DEAL WAS FOR 200.

584
00:40:56,246 --> 00:40:58,290
TESSIC: OUR DEAL WAS
FOR POWER CELLS,

585
00:40:58,331 --> 00:41:01,293
MEDICAL SUPPLIES,
AND REPAIR WORK.

586
00:41:01,334 --> 00:41:04,587
YOU PROVIDED US
WITH MUCH MORE THAN THAT.

587
00:41:04,629 --> 00:41:08,674
SECOND MAN: BESIDES, WE SEEM TO
HAVE A SURPLUS FOR THE MOMENT.

588
00:41:08,716 --> 00:41:10,969
TESSIC: GIVE YOUR CREW
OUR THANKS.

589
00:41:11,010 --> 00:41:13,512
ARCHER: HAVE A GOOD SEASON.
